cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is about Reinforcement Learning (RL) and specifically focuses on Reinforcement Learning from Demonstrations (RLfD), which is a subfield of RL. The paper discusses the issue of imperfect demonstrations and proposes a method to address it. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of demonstrations in computer vision tasks, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision) a likely category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the optimization problem and the use of a dual form, which suggests that cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant category.
